Key Match Events: Stunning Bounedjah strike ruled out for offside.
Angola hold on for a point after coming from behind.
Pre-Game Insights: Algeria are looking to bounce back from their AFCON horror show two years ago when they crashed out in the group-stage, finishing bottom with just one point and one goal to their name.

It is 12 years since Angola last won an AFCON match, but they come into this match on the back of four consecutive goalless draws, suggesting they are capable of making it a frustrating night for Algeria.
Post-Match Reflections: More frustration at AFCON for Algeria, following on from their results two years ago.
Angola had to come from behind to get a result, really impressive from them. They'll be believing they can reach the knockout stages.
